## ðŸš€ Quick Start

### Installation

```bash
# First of all, install python 3.9+ (Not tested on older versions)
# Then you can install either from pypy or testpypi
pip install lunaengine
pip install -i https://test.pypi.org/simple/ lunaengine
```

*Ignore*
```bash
# Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Run a basic example
python examples/ui_comprehensive_demo.py
```

## Requirements

### Core Dependencies (required):

```bash
pygame>=2.5.0
numpy>=1.21.0
PyOpenGL>=3.1.0
PyOpenGL-accelerate>=3.1.0
PyOpenAL
```

### Development Tools (optional):

```bash
black>=22.0.0
flake8>=4.0.0
pytest>=7.0.0
setuptools>=65.0.0
wheel>=0.37.0
twine>=4.0.0
```

## Build
```bash
# Make build
python -m build

# Check files
twine check dist/* 

# Upload testpypi
twine upload --config-file .pypirc --repository testpypi dist/*

# Upload PyPi
twine upload --config-file .pypirc --repository pypi dist/*
```

## OpenGL
- Require OpenGL 2.0+
- OpenGL come actvated by default

